Description: The North Carolina map displays several private schools near the cities of Raleigh, Wilmington, and Asheville.     There is an outlier, however, in the North Eastern part of North Carolina. This could be from high agriculture production making few people that live in the area causing the government to not fund for public schools, which makes funding for private schools necessary.
Media Credit: Source: USGS, Tiger Line, IES - NCES, NC One Map, US Census Bureau

Description: From the poverty spread, North Carolina represents a strong correlation between the location of private schools and higher income communities.     The amount of people above the various poverty levels are represented near the cities and the cities from the previous map shown exemplify private schools.
Media Credit: Source: USGS, Tiger Line, IES - NCES, NC One Map, US Census Bureau

Description: Wake County has several private schools listed in it.     It has almost an equal amount of private schools as there public schools in the area.     It needs all of these schools because it holds the city of Raleigh and several hundreds of thousands of people live there.
Media Credit: Source: USGS, Tiger Line, IES - NCES, NC One Map, US Census Bureau

Description: Wake County is an econopmically feasible area to live in.     It holds hundred of thousnads of people in it and displays thousands of people well over the poverty line.     It speaks to the correlation of private schools being near the city due to Wake COunty holding Raleigh and the high amount of prosperous people.
Media Credit: Source: USGS, Tiger Line, IES - NCES, NC One Map, US Census Bureau

Description: Illinois has very few private schools.     Most of the private schools listed in Illinois take place in Cook County where Chicago is, Rockford, East St. Louis and Springfield.     There is an outlier in the souther tip of Illinois, which can result from needing private systems due to the low population from agricultural land being there and the state government not wanting to fund these areas
Media Credit: Source: USGS, Tiger Line, IES - NCES, NC One Map, US Census Bureau

Description: From the poverty spread, Illinois represents a strong correlation between the location of private schools and higher income communities.     Cook County and even Rockford are the two highest earning communities and cna be shown in the poverty spread maps.     These two areas have the most amount of private schoola in the state of Illinois and makes sense for the income involved there.
Media Credit: Source: USGS, Tiger Line, IES - NCES, NC One Map, US Census Bureau
